  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_surfaceSymmetry">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_surfaceSymmetry</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Axiomatic derivation of the Surface Symmetry Theorem. Holds at all quantum levels: the composite P∘Π∘G is a well-typed morphism whenever G and P share the same state:Frame. Follows from the definition of the shared-frame condition and the type-equivalence algebra.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/surfaceSymmetry"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_CC_1">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_CC_1</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof that a CompleteType T satisfies: resolution(x, T) terminates in O(1) for all x ∈ R_n. Follows from IT_7d: when χ(N(C)) = n and all β_k = 0, the resolver has no topological obstructions.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/CC_1"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_CC_2">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_CC_2</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof that the ψ pipeline is monotone: each constraint application cannot increase the site deficit. Derived from the definition of the partition refinement order.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/CC_2"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_CC_3">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_CC_3</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof that a CompletenessCertificate implies CompleteType: the certificate attestation is only issued when IT_7d holds, by construction of the CompletenessResolver.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/CC_3"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_CC_4">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_CC_4</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof that the CompletenessAuditTrail witnessCount equals the number of CompletenessWitness records in the trail. Structural invariant of the audit accumulation protocol.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/CC_4"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_CC_5">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_CC_5</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof that the CechNerve nerve computation is deterministic: the same constraint set always produces the same nerve topology. Follows from the nerve functor being a functor (functoriality).</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/CC_5"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/EulerPoincare"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_1">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_QL_1</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Universal proof that neg(bnot(x)) = succ(x) in Z/(2^n)Z for all n ≥ 1. Derived symbolically from ring axioms: bnot is bitwise complement, neg is two&apos;s complement negation, succ is modular increment. The critical identity in universal form.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/QL_1"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_2">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_QL_2</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Universal proof that the ring carrier set size is exactly 2^n for all n ≥ 1. Follows from the definition of Z/(2^n)Z.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/QL_2"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_3">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_QL_3</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Universal proof that Landauer erasure cost scales as n × k_B T ln 2 at quantum level n. Follows from the thermodynamic interpretation: each bit erased from an n-bit ring costs k_B T ln 2.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/QL_3"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_4">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_QL_4</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Universal proof that the dihedral group D_{2^n} action on Z/(2^n)Z is faithful for all n ≥ 1. The stabilizer of any element is trivial under the full dihedral action.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/QL_4"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_5">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_QL_5</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Universal proof that canonical form rewriting terminates at all quantum levels. The rewriting system is terminating by lexicographic descent on the term complexity measure.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/QL_5"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_6">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_QL_6</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Universal proof that the completeness criterion χ(N(C)) = n generalizes to all quantum levels. Derived from the definition of the nerve construction and the Euler characteristic formula for simplicial complexes.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/QL_6"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QL_7">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_QL_7</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Universal proof of the ring topology Euler characteristic identity: χ = 1 − n at quantum level n. Derived from the CW decomposition of the n-dimensional torus formed by the ring&apos;s cyclic group action.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/QL_7"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/EulerPoincare"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_GR_1">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_GR_1</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of binding monotonicity: freeRank(B_{i+1}) ≤ freeRank(B_i) for all i in a Session. Follows from the definition of the BindingAccumulator: each appended binding either pins sites or is a no-op; it never frees them.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/GR_1"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_GR_2">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_GR_2</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof that the empty session is the identity element of the session algebra: freeRank(B_0) = total site space. The empty accumulator has no pinned sites by definition.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/GR_2"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_GR_3">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_GR_3</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of session convergence: a session terminates iff freeRank reaches its minimum (the maximum pinned by the given constraint set). Follows from the compactness of the site space and monotonicity.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/GR_3"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_GR_4">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_GR_4</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof that disjoint bindings compose without site conflict: if two bindings address disjoint site sets, their composition is well-defined and their union is also a valid binding.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/GR_4"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_GR_5">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_GR_5</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of contradiction detection correctness: ContradictionBoundary fires iff there exist bindings b, b&apos; in the same Context with the same address, different datum, and same constraint. This is the minimal condition for type contradiction.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/GR_5"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_1">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_TS_1</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of nerve realisability: for any target profile with χ* ≤ n and β₀* = 1, there exists a ConstrainedType whose constraint nerve realises the target. Follows from the constructive synthesis algorithm.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/TS_1"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_2">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_TS_2</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of minimal basis bound: the MinimalConstraintBasis for the IT_7d target has size exactly n. Follows from the site-by-site construction and the minimality criterion.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/TS_2"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_3">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_TS_3</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of synthesis monotonicity: adding a constraint never decreases the Euler characteristic of the constraint nerve. Follows from the nerve inclusion principle.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/TS_3"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_4">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_TS_4</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of synthesis convergence: the TypeSynthesisResolver terminates in at most n steps. Follows from monotonicity (TS_3) and the finite site budget bound.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/TS_4"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_5">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_TS_5</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of synthesis-certification duality: a SynthesizedType achieves IT_7d iff the CompletenessResolver certifies it as CompleteType. The duality follows from the shared topological criterion.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/TS_5"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_6">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_TS_6</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of Jacobian-guided synthesis efficiency: the Jacobian oracle reduces expected steps from O(n²) to O(n log n). Follows from the information content of the Jacobian at each synthesis step.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/TS_6"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_TS_7">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_TS_7</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of unreachable signatures: β₀ = 0 is unreachable by any non-empty ConstrainedType. Follows from the nerve connectedness of non-empty constraint sets.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/TS_7"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_1">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_1</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of lift unobstructedness criterion: WittLift T&apos; is CompleteType iff the spectral sequence collapses at E_2. Follows from the Leray spectral sequence of the quantum level extension.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_1"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/baseCase rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_1_base"/>
    <uor:proof/inductiveStep rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_6"/>
    <uor:proof/validForKAtLeast rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</uor:proof/validForKAtLeast>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/BitwiseInduction"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_2">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_2</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of obstruction localisation: a non-trivial LiftObstruction is localised to a specific site at bit position n+1. Follows from the local-to-global structure of the constraint nerve.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_2"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/baseCase rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_2_base"/>
    <uor:proof/inductiveStep rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_2_step"/>
    <uor:proof/validForKAtLeast rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</uor:proof/validForKAtLeast>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/BitwiseInduction"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_3">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_3</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of monotone lifting: basisSize(T&apos;) = basisSize(T) + 1 for trivially obstructed lifts. Follows from the minimal basis construction at Q_{n+1}.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_3"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/baseCase rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_3_base"/>
    <uor:proof/inductiveStep rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_3_step"/>
    <uor:proof/validForKAtLeast rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</uor:proof/validForKAtLeast>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/BitwiseInduction"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_4">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_4</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of spectral sequence convergence bound: the spectral sequence converges by page E_{d+2} for depth-d configurations. Follows from the filtration length of the constraint nerve chain complex.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_4"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/baseCase rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_4_base"/>
    <uor:proof/inductiveStep rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_4_step"/>
    <uor:proof/validForKAtLeast rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</uor:proof/validForKAtLeast>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/BitwiseInduction"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_5">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_5</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of universal identity preservation under quantum lifts: every universallyValid identity holds in the lifted ring. Follows from the universal validity definition and ring extension properties.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_5"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/baseCase rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_5_base"/>
    <uor:proof/inductiveStep rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_6"/>
    <uor:proof/validForKAtLeast rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</uor:proof/validForKAtLeast>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/BitwiseInduction"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_6">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/InductiveProof"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_6</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of ψ-pipeline universality for quantum lifts: the ψ-pipeline produces a valid ChainComplex for any WittLift. Follows from the functorial construction of the chain complex.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_6"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/baseCase rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_6_base"/>
    <uor:proof/inductiveStep rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_6_step"/>
    <uor:proof/validForKAtLeast rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</uor:proof/validForKAtLeast>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/BitwiseInduction"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_1_base">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_1_base</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Base case for QLS_1 at Q0: lift unobstructedness holds trivially for 8-bit rings where the constraint nerve is contractible.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_1"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">false</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_2_base">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_2_base</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Base case for QLS_2 at Q0: obstruction localisation holds at the 8-bit level where sites are directly inspectable.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_2"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">false</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_2_step">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_2_step</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Inductive step for QLS_2: if obstruction is localised at Q_k, the local-to-global structure of the constraint nerve preserves localisation at Q_{k+1}.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_2"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_3_base">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_3_base</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Base case for QLS_3 at Q0: monotone lifting basis size increment holds trivially for 8-bit to 16-bit extension.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_3"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">false</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_3_step">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_3_step</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Inductive step for QLS_3: the minimal basis construction at Q_{k+1} adds exactly one element from the trivially obstructed site.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_3"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_4_base">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_4_base</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Base case for QLS_4 at Q0: spectral sequence convergence at E_{d+2} holds for 8-bit filtrations by direct computation.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_4"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">false</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_4_step">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_4_step</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Inductive step for QLS_4: filtration length at Q_{k+1} extends by at most one page from Q_k, preserving the E_{d+2} bound.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_4"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_5_base">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_5_base</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Base case for QLS_5 at Q0: universallyValid identities hold in the 8-bit ring by definition of universal validity.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_5"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">false</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_6_base">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_6_base</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Base case for QLS_6 at Q0: the psi-pipeline produces a valid ChainComplex for 8-bit WittLifts by direct construction.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_6"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">false</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WLS_6_step">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WLS_6_step</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Inductive step for QLS_6: the functorial construction of the chain complex commutes with quantum level extension.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WLS_6"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WT_3_base">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WT_3_base</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Base case for QT_3: resolved basis size formula holds for chain length 1 by direct construction.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WT_3"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">false</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_WT_5_base">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_WT_5_base</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Base case for QT_5: LiftChainCertificate existence for tower height 1 follows from single-step certificate issuance.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/WT_5"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">false</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_AR_5_base">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_AR_5_base</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Base case for AR_5 at Q0: greedy vs adiabatic cost difference verified by exhaustive enumeration over Z/256Z.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/AR_5"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">false</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_AR_5_step">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_AR_5_step</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Inductive step for AR_5: if greedy vs adiabatic bound holds at Q_k, it holds at Q_{k+1} by QLS_5 (universal identity preservation under quantum lift).</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/AR_5"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QM_6_base">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_QM_6_base</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Base case for QM_6 at Q0: amplitude index set equals monotone pinning trajectories by exhaustive trajectory enumeration over the 8-bit site lattice.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/QM_6"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">false</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_QM_6_step">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_QM_6_step</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Inductive step for QM_6: monotone pinning trajectories at Q_{k+1} extend those at Q_k by the site lattice ordering (monotone extension property).</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/QM_6"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_1">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_MN_1</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of holonomy group containment: HolonomyGroup(T) ≤ D_{2^n}. Follows from the fact that all constraint applications are dihedral group elements.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/MN_1"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/EulerPoincare"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_2">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_MN_2</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of additive flatness: additive constraints (ResidueConstraint, DepthConstraint) generate only the identity in D_{2^n}. Follows from the additive structure of the dihedral action.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/MN_2"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/EulerPoincare"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_3">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_MN_3</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of dihedral generation: neg and bnot together generate D_{2^n}. Follows from the standard presentation of the dihedral group by involutions.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/MN_3"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/EulerPoincare"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_4">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_MN_4</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of holonomy-Betti implication: non-trivial holonomy implies β₁ ≥ 1. Follows from the fact that a non-trivial monodromy requires a topological loop in the constraint nerve.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/MN_4"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/EulerPoincare"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_5">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_MN_5</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of CompleteType holonomy: IT_7d (β₁ = 0) implies trivial holonomy (FlatType). Follows from MN_4 contrapositive: trivial holonomy ← β₁ = 0.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/MN_5"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/EulerPoincare"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_6">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_MN_6</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of monodromy composition: the monodromy map is a group homomorphism from the loop space to D_{2^n}. Follows from the composition of dihedral group elements.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/MN_6"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/EulerPoincare"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_MN_7">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_MN_7</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of TwistedType obstruction class: a TwistedType always contributes a non-zero class to H²(N(C(T&apos;)); ℤ/2ℤ) for any WittLift T&apos;. Follows from MN_4 and the obstruction theory of dihedral torsors.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/MN_7"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/EulerPoincare"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_PT_1">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_PT_1</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of PT_1: product type site additivity. siteBudget(A × B) = siteBudget(A) + siteBudget(B). Follows from the definition of ProductType as an independent concatenation of site spaces.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/PT_1"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_PT_2">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_PT_2</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of PT_2: product type partition factorisation. partition(A × B) = partition(A) ⊗ partition(B). Follows from the tensor product structure of constraint nerves over independent site spaces.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/PT_2"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/EulerPoincare"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_PT_3">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_PT_3</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of PT_3: product type Euler characteristic additivity. χ(N(C(A × B))) = χ(N(C(A))) + χ(N(C(B))). Follows from the Künneth formula applied to the join of constraint nerves.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/PT_3"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Composition"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_PT_4">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_PT_4</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of PT_4: product type entropy additivity. S(A × B) = S(A) + S(B). Follows from PT_1 (site additivity) and TH_1 (S = freeRank × ln 2).</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/PT_4"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_ST_1">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_ST_1</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of ST_1: sum type site budget maximum. siteBudget(A + B) = max(siteBudget(A), siteBudget(B)). Follows from SumType requiring capacity for the larger variant.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/ST_1"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_ST_2">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_ST_2</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of ST_2: sum type entropy. S(A + B) = ln 2 + max(S(A), S(B)). The ln 2 term accounts for the variant discriminant bit; the max reflects that only one variant is active at a time.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/ST_2"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_GS_1">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_GS_1</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of SC_1: context temperature. T_ctx(C) = freeRank(C) × ln 2 / n. Derived from TH_1 normalized per site.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/GS_1"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_GS_2">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_GS_2</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of SC_2: saturation degree. σ(C) = (n − freeRank(C)) / n. Definitional identity.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/GS_2"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_GS_3">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_GS_3</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of SC_3: saturation monotonicity. Corollary of SR_1 through order-reversing SC_2.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/GS_3"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/RingAxiom"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_GS_4">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_GS_4</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of SC_4: ground state equivalence. Four equivalent conditions for full saturation derived from SC_2, TH_1, SC_1.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/GS_4"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_GS_5">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/AxiomaticDerivation"/>
    <rdfs:label>prf_GS_5</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Proof of SC_5: O(1) resolution guarantee at saturation. Derived from SR_2 and FreeRank.isClosed at freeRank = 0.</rdfs:comment>
    <uor:proof/provesIdentity rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/op/GS_5"/>
    <uor:proof/universalScope rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/universalScope>
    <uor:proof/verified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</uor:proof/verified>
    <uor:proof/strategy rdf:resource="https://uor.foundation/proof/Simplification"/>
  </owl:NamedIndividual>

  <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://uor.foundation/proof/prf_GS_6">
